Package search

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Action
    The Action interface encapsulates the concept of an action taken from a particular State.
    EditableFrontier
    An Editable Frontier is a Frontier from which you can remove nodes according to their terminal state as well as according to the defined remove operation
    Frontier
    A Frontier encapsulates the collection of search Nodes (not States!) that are on the frontier of a frontier search (i.e.
    GoalTest
    An interface encapsulating the concept of a test that checks whether a given state is a valid goal state.
    InferenceGoalTest
    Inference Goal Tests extend Goal Tests to provide the opportunity to check whether a given state could possibly lead to a goal state.
    NodeFunction
    An Interface that encapsulates the concept of a function on Nodes which can be used to provide heuristic functions amongst other things.
    PathConstraint
    Path Constraints encapsulate the concept of a constraint on the path that is defined by a node.
    Search
    The Search interface encapsulates the notion of a search algorithm which seeks a solution for reaching a State that satisfies a Goal Test by starting from a root State and pursuing actions to reach new states until a goal State is found or until no further new States can be reached.
    State
    State encapsulates the notion of a state which has potential actions that transition to other states.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AStarFunction
    The A* function provides an implementation of a NodeFunction which will be used for A* search The heuristic function used will need to be admissible and consistent
    BestFirstFrontier
    A Frontier that implements the concept of providing the "best" node among those in the frontier as it's next output node.
    BreadthFirstFrontier
    Implementation of a Breadth First Frontier which provides nodes in FIFO order
    DepthFirstFrontier
    Implementation of a Depth First Frontier providing Nodes in a LIFO order
    FrontierSearch
    Abstract class providing the structure of search as performed in graph and tree search and similar Frontier based search algorithms.
    GraphSearch
    An implementation of the Graph Search algorithm.
    IterativeDeepeningTreeSearch
    Implementation of Iterative Deepening Search which loops depth first search to a depth limit before incrementing the depth limit and searching again for a solution.
    Node
    Node class which encapsulates the concept of a node in a search that has a current state that has been reached from a parent node's state by taking a particular action
    PathActionCountConstraint
    A Path Action Count Constraint is a constraint on the precise number of actions along a node's ancestral action path
    PathActionCountUpperConstraint
    Path Action Count Upper Constraint is a upper bound constraint on the total number of actions on the ancestral action path specified by a given node
    PathCostFunction
    The path distance returns function gives the total cumulative cost of the actions along the node's ancestral action path
    PathCostUpperConstraint
    Path Cost Upper Constraint is an upper bound constraint on the total cost of the ancestral action path specified by a node
    Printing
    An abstract class providing a framework for printing search solutions To implement it a client must implement the printing of individual states and actions.
    TreeSearch
    Tree Search implements the tree search algorithm.
    UniformCostGraphSearch
    An implementation of the Uniform Cost Graph Search Algorithm which always provides a minimum cost solution
